<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════
     5. KEY THINGS TO KNOW (Tabs)
═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section class="cd-tabs">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>Key Things to Know</h2>
    <div class="cd-tabs__wrap">
      <div class="cd-tabs__nav">
        <button class="tab-btn active" data-tab="1">Scalability<i class="fas fa-chevron-right tab-arrow"></i></button>
        <button class="tab-btn" data-tab="2">Security & Compliance<i class="fas fa-chevron-right tab-arrow"></i></button>
        <button class="tab-btn" data-tab="3">Integration<i class="fas fa-chevron-right tab-arrow"></i></button>
        <button class="tab-btn" data-tab="4">Migration Strategy<i class="fas fa-chevron-right tab-arrow"></i></button>
        <button class="tab-btn" data-tab="5">Support & Maintenance<i class="fas fa-chevron-right tab-arrow"></i></button>
      </div>
      <div class="cd-tabs__content">
        <div class="tab-panel active" data-panel="1">
          <p>Enterprise software must grow alongside your organization. The Demski Group architects systems on proven cloud-native patterns — horizontal scaling, microservices, and managed databases — so your platform handles ten times the load tomorrow without a costly rebuild.</p>
          <p>We define clear scaling boundaries from day one, instrument performance from the start, and choose technologies proven under enterprise load, ensuring your system never becomes the bottleneck as your business expands.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tab-panel" data-panel="2">
          <p>Enterprise environments carry strict security obligations. We implement defense-in-depth strategies: network segmentation, zero-trust access policies, end-to-end encryption, and comprehensive audit trails that satisfy the most demanding internal security reviews and external compliance audits.</p>
          <p>Whether your organization must meet SOC 2, HIPAA, GDPR, or ISO 27001, the Demski Group integrates compliance into the architecture rather than bolting it on after the fact.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tab-panel" data-panel="3">
          <p>Large organizations run dozens of systems that must share data reliably. The Demski Group specializes in enterprise integration — designing event-driven architectures, RESTful and GraphQL APIs, and ETL pipelines that connect your ERP, CRM, HRIS, and third-party tools into a coherent data ecosystem.</p>
          <p>We handle authentication, rate limiting, error handling, and contract versioning so your integrations remain reliable as upstream systems change — eliminating the fragile point-to-point connections that plague legacy enterprise environments.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tab-panel" data-panel="4">
          <p>Moving from a legacy system to modern enterprise software is one of the highest-risk projects an organization can undertake. The Demski Group mitigates that risk through phased migration strategies, parallel running periods, and comprehensive data validation, ensuring continuity throughout the transition.</p>
          <p>We document every legacy business rule before a single line of new code is written, perform data reconciliation at every migration milestone, and provide rollback plans so your team has confidence at every step of the journey.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tab-panel" data-panel="5">
          <p>Enterprise systems require ongoing stewardship. The Demski Group provides structured support agreements that include proactive monitoring, security patching, performance reviews, and feature development — keeping your platform aligned with your evolving business needs without the overhead of managing it in-house.</p>
          <p>Our support model scales from on-call incident response to dedicated development retainers, giving you the coverage level your business-critical systems require.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

